It would be useful in some cases to be able to external import data into Confluence Blueprints.

I'm raising this feature request on behalf of a customer who reached out to us via a Support ticket. Please see the quoted text below from the customer on their use case. The use case here is specific to the Product Requirements Blueprint, but may be applied to encompass other Blueprints as well.

{quote}
We have a list of requirements in a document. It would be nice to be able to import these requirements into Confluence and have those requirements turned into requirement blueprints. Given that we have over 1,000 requirements, manually creating 1,000 wiki pages based off the Requirements Blueprint is not realistic.

Perhaps something similar to the Jira CSV importer. We could export all of our requirements into a CSV file and then import that CSV file into Confluence to have the Requirements Blueprint pages created for us. Even if you guys defined how the CSV file needed to look, it would still be far easier than manually entering in 1,000's of requirements by hand.
{quote}

