While trying to add new user to Confluence users by SOAP method "addUser(sessionId, userEmail, userFullName, userName, userUrl, userPassword)" a new user adds, but the application access flags are not set according to Default Application Access.

To reproduce a bug do the following:
- create new Confluence OnDemand + JIRA (name it "example"), set administrator user/password;
- use SOAP to login as administrator (for example, from here: [Generic Soap Client|http://www.soapclient.com/soaptest.html] with WSDL file from here: [https://example.atlassian.net/wiki/rpc/soap-axis/confluenceservice-v1?wsdl]); remember sessionId;
- use SOAP to add new User. Specify stored sessionId and any valid user data. Invoke the request.
- Login to just created Confluence OnDemand. Goto "User Management" - "Application Access". *No applications' checkboxes set*, instead of "Default Application Access" contains "JIRA".

