Given that issue CONF-7526 was opened in 2006, just hosed me out of several hours of work, has been voted on by 23 people, and is currently unassigned, there is a bigger problem here, which is that important bugs are being ignored.

The fix for this is straightforward and obviously needed.

h5. Steps to reproduce:
# Access Confluence using Chrome/FF
# Create a page & add Code Macro
# Paste the following code into the Code Macro:
{quote}
<xsl:variable name="userMapping" select="mx:execute-formula('public.ECN.import.primetrade.match.users', concat('User:',normalize-space($userLabel)))"></xsl:variable>
{quote}
# Result: Nothing is pasted into the Code Macro but instead the browser just freezed/hanged

h5. Workaround:
# Use IE as an alternative browser to paste the code successfully into the Code Macro frame and the code will be rendered just fine and browser won't crashed.
# Insert the code using wiki markup instead:
{quote}
{code}
<xsl:variable name="userMapping" select="mx:execute-formula('public.ECN.import.primetrade.match.users', concat('User:',normalize-space($userLabel)))"></xsl:variable>
{code}
{quote}
